title: Escort to Namtok
description: A husband and wife hire Tim and Toubo to guide them through a jungle infested with dangerous animals and headhunters.

title: The Gaboon Viper
description: Tim and Toubo are hired by a big game hunter to guide him into remote African territory so he can hunt and photograph a secret native ritual involving poisonous snakes.

title: The Runaway King
description: Tim and Toubo become intrigued by reports of an island whose visitors are said never to return.

title: The Lady of Rajmahal
description: Tim and Toubo are hired to transport a valuable painting through the jungle.

title: The Greatest Beast
description: Tim and Toubo investigate the disappearance of man who was supposedly slain by a monstrous animal.

title: Gypsy Prince
description: Tim and Toubo are asked to return a young man to his real family so he can claim his rightful place as Prince of the Gypsy.

title: Old Lady's Mine
description: An elderly woman hires Tim and Toubo to guide her to a her gold mine deep in the Central American jungle. She plans to investigate the sudden drop in production.

title: Return of the Hawk
description: A wealthy man hires Tim and Toubo as bodyguards to protect his family from a bandit gang who is terrorizing the area.

title: Jungle Rebel
description: In French Indo-China, Tim and Toubo are hired to negotiate a peace treaty between the French and a rebel band operating near Saigon.

title: Cut Charlie In
description: Tim and Toubo become friends with a war hero, but the man is actually a liar and a criminal

title: Pearls Off Dondra Head
description: Tim and Toubo learn of a rich pearl bed from a dying man and decide to try their luck at pearl diving.

title: Jungle Search
description: Tim and Toubo are hired to locate a missing plane which disappeared into the Indian jungle carrying vital medicine. They are not the only searchers, however; two black marketeers are seeking the missing cargo, too.

title: Hate at Forty Fathoms
description: Tim and Toubo are hired to kill a whale responsible for the deaths of numerous fishermen.

title: Malayan Magic
description: Tim and Toubo use magic tricks and an old cane to challenge a despotic Malayan ruler who routinely kills those who oppose him.

title: Torch of Olympiad
description: Tim and Toubu visit Crete to search for a relic over three thousand years old called "The Torch of the Olympiad".

title: Walk Wide of Lions
description: A doctor hires Tim and Toulo to guide him to a African chieftain in desperate need of medical attention, but the chief's rivals want to prevent the operation.

title: The General
description: Tim and Toulo investigate South American revolutionaries.

title: The Elephant Gun
description: Tim and Toubo investigate the death of a friend who was supposedly killed by an elephant on a rampage.

title: Bite of the Ruby Red
description: Two scientists hire Tim and Toubo to help them find a Central American tribe who are said to have a natural immunity to the deadly bite of a tick called "The Ruby Red."

title: The Honor of Dr. Mazaro
description: A chemical company hires to Tim and Toubo to negotiate the renewal of a contract with the leader of a Latin American country.

title: Girl in the Jeep
description: While sitting in a bar in Algiers, Tim and Toubo become fascinated with a beautiful girl.

title: The Vanishing Island
description: Tim and Toubo attempt to locate a mysterious island that is said to appear and disappear.

title: Run 'Till You Die
description: Tim and Toubo assist an Asian plantation owner from the attacks of Tibetan bandits.

title: Last Days of Dolores
description: Tim and Toubo are hired to find a research scientist who failed to return from an expedition in remote Mexico.

title: Escape from Camp Diablo
description: Tim and Toubo try to prove the existence of a notorious, and illegal, prison.

title: The Black Scarab
description: Tim and Toubo try to help a lovely French woman whose son has been kidnapped by her brutal husband.

title: The Lady and the Lion
description: After a series of accidents disrupt production, a movie company working in Africa hires Tim and Toubo to protect the crew.

title: Drums of Far Island
description: While on a fishing trip to the Virgin Islands, Tim and Toubo uncover a voodoo revival.

title: Aloha Means Goodbye
description: Tim and Toubo are unwelcome party crashers on an exclusive Hawaiian island.

title: Massacre in Mokhara
description: When a friend requests their help Tim and Toubo journey to Tibet, but are attacked en route by bandits.

title: The Greater Magic
description: A professor hires Tim and Toubo to help locate a supposed lost tribe of white aborigines in a remote part of New Guinea.

title: Limehouse Knights
description: While visiting London, Tim and Toubo help Scotland Yard investigate a gang of jewel smugglers.

title: The Monster of Loch Mac Gora
description: Tim and Toubo search for the lost writings of James Boswell and a legendary monster while visiting a remote Scottish castle.

title: The Black Cat Waits
description: Two women hire Tom and Toubo to help them find men whose plane crashed in the Amazon jungle.

title: Boomerang
description: An Australian policeman insists Tim and Toubo interrupt their gold mining operations to help him captured an escaped convict.

title: River of Death
description: Tim and Toubo are hired to find a prospector thought lost in the Amazonian jungle. Their search is hindered by a tribe of angry headhunters.

title: Treasure of Vickers' Island
description: Struck by a hurricane in the South Pacific, Tim and Toubo's ship is wrecked on a remote island.

title: The Tattooed Lady of Torima
description: Tim and Toubo investigate emerald smuggling in a small South American town.

title: Doubled in Diamonds
description: A niece and a chief of security conspire to murder a South African diamond mine owner so the niece can inherit the pit.

title: The Danger Sisters
description: A sister knife-throwing act working in North Africa hire Tim and Toubo as bodyguards.

title: Hatchet Man
description: Tim and Toubo are hired to smuggle a Chinese gentleman out of England, not knowing that man is actually a leader of the London rackets pursued by the police.

title: Slave Market
description: Tim is captured and sold in an Arabian slave auction. Toubo desperately tries to organize a rescue.

title: Temple of Terror
description: Tim and Toubo are hired by a beautiful native girl to find her archaeologist boyfriend who is missing somewhere in the Indo-China jungle.

title: Attack at Ras El Ma
description: While in Algers working for an oil company, Tim and Toubo are caught in a revolt of Arab tribesmen against the French colonial government.

title: Guns for El Khadar
description: Tim and Toubo help the French Foreign Legion track down the men responsible for arming hostile Arab tribesmen.

title: Skull of the Inca
description: A archaeologist hires Tim and Toubo to guide him to an ancient Inca ruin deep in the jungle.

title: Pipeline to Danger
description: Tim and Toubo are hired to find out the cause in the loss of production in an Arabian oil field. The first thing they discover is a murder.

title: The Green Trap
description: Tim and Toubo are leading an African safari not realizing that one of their party is suffering from an emotional breakdown.

title: A Gift of Death
description: While visiting Kenya, Tim and Toubo are hired to capture a prize lion.

title: Sandhogs
description: When a construction foreman runs into trouble building a tunnel under a Cuban harbor, he hires Tim and Toubo to find who is sabotaging his work.

title: The City of Doom
description: Tim and Toubo are hired to help a construction workers battle a cult who believes their gods will destroy their Far Eastern city if their building project is finished.

title: Crew of the Dolly 'D'
description: Tim and Toubo are hired to protect a ship's valuable cargo and must battle mutineers who want to take over the vessel.
